title: Taevalaul aka Sky Song  (2010)
description:
Plot:  Soon to close the Tallinn Black Nights Film Festival is Mati KÃƒÂ¼tt's forty five minute stop motion animation Sky Song. It looks to be a highly experimental piece of the sort that should appeal to fans of Jan Svankmajer. Here's how the festival describes it:

It is an ode for all of those who like to fly. Is it possible to reach the Moon in one breath? Yes, it is if you have the will to fly and the appropriate training. This is the case with postman Rain. This is not simply the journey of a postman to deliver the package to the Moon. It is also a philosophical journey in time and eras, through people and their characters, through thoughts and imagination.
